This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it discusses linguistic theory and the validity of a mathematical model for word order. It may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it mentions the cost of a dependency as a function of its length. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses psychological bias in linguistic research. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Computation and Language (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) due to its focus on dependency length and cost.
